results.adr_address: 4917 US-90, Pace, FL 32571-1408, USA
results.name: Ruby Tuesday

reviews.text: Outstanding place to eat a lunch or a dinner.  Service is marvelous and they make the elderly so comfortable with the treatment  as a valuable person. They have a great menu and salad bar. Price is right and with a coupon a meal becomes a bargain.  Go there, spend time and have fun.

The food is always delicious and Makenna is a great sever/bartender! She makes for good company and a great drink. Also the hostess always helps me with the door so I can get the baby stroller in without struggling.

I love their salad bar and they have awesome Hickory barbacue ribs. There was no waiting, very quick and friendly service from staff & waitress. We went on a Wed. just around 11am and had great food & service. I would highly recommend Ruby Tuesdays to others for a fast & friendly family dining experience!

I'm sorry to say that the visit wasn't the best that we have had. The lettuce was kind of old looking and many of the salad plates were not clean. But the food that we ordered was very good and the staff was very good. Probably just an off day for the dishwasher. It's always been a good place to eat. We will return.

Had lunch there a couple of hours ago, service was poor, salad was vertically uneatable, rusty lettuce, cherry tomatoes that where hard and taste less. Went to Ruby Tuesday because of a come on that they mailed to us, which this Ruby Tuesday would not accept. Won‚Äôt be going back!
,

results.adr_address: 4475 Woodbine Rd #1, Pace, FL 33570, USA
results.name: Hungry Howie's Pizza

reviews.text: Love their pizzas and wed crazy 5$ food

Really friendly service. I went there two days in a row while attending a conference down the street. Clean, ample parking, decent prices. Minus one star because they don't have paper towels in the bathroom, and only offer one of those lousy hand dryers.
It was ok I've had better I ordered the steak and mushroom sub it was mostly just bread not much of any thing else
My order showed up early. Was totally correct even though I had changed several toppings on my salads. The delivery driver was very nice. Everything was packed properly and the food was good.
Good, fast service, but it seems most times when we go in that a manager or some employee is shouting angrily at another and it makes for an awkward time sitting at the store.

results.adr_address: 5023 US-90, Pace, FL 32571, USA
results.name: Chick-fil-A

reviews.text: Took the grandchildren there to celebrate their report cards.  Thank you for the great food and family atmosphere.
Always a great choice when we come down south!  I got the grilled chicken sandwich

Another great Chick-fil-A with great food and great service. Employee Dillon S. Was super helpful attending the register and the tables around the restaurant. He even noticed before I did that I had ordered a free cup of water but hadn't received it yet. Thank you Dillon for your helpfulness!

Love this place. Staff is great and they thank military folks for their service. Where else do you see this now. Food is always great and I love their waffle fries. They also support their communities during storms. In Alabama they actually gave away free food to people who were stranded during a snow storm

By far my fave!!  And their app is great!  Earn freebies plus receive them from Chick-fil-A, just because!!  I‚Äôve had a fair share of free meals and have only been using the app a few months.  Love everything about Chick-fil-A‚Äôs FOOD!!!!

results.adr_address: 4763 US-90, Pace, FL 32571, USA
results.name: Panera Bread

reviews.text: A rich white girls Paradise. I'm just kidding but in all seriousness the food tastes very fresh as they live up to the company standards. All of the bakeries tasted amazing also. The dining room was also cleaned and kept that way

I would give five stars but I feel like the portion sizes are always a little small, especially with the soup.  Love the food, tastes amazing!  Great service.  Five stars for those things, just not portions.  My boyfriend paid for a bread bowl and got less soup then I did in my cup, and I didn't get very much.  Very disappointing.

Despite the TV commercials about Panera Bread offering delivery - this one doesn't. At least not yet. But that's not the reason they're only getting three stars. They're getting three stars because the value of what you get vs what you pay for just isn't really there.

I feel like a lot of my money is going towards atmosphere whenever I eat here (most recently about a week ago) instead of towards portions or even really quality of food. It's alright food, don't get me wrong. Solidly worth the visit. It's just nothing that is going to make you think "Wow, what a great meal!" like you might expect from a traditional dine-in experience.
Pretty damn good!! Loved my Fuji apple salad. I was hoping for more gf options. Only one soup was, the Turkey chili. It was good. But not what I wanted. I'll be back though.
Great atmosphere.  My sandwich was made incorrectly. Without going into detail. They gave me a new sandwich.

results.adr_address: 4880 US-90, Pace, FL 32571, USA
results.name: Panda Express

reviews.text: Rude staff, just were standing around when I came in, acted like I was a pest for asking about my food that I ordered 40 mins prior. Claimed they just got it when it was sitting there I  the printer when I got there and no one was even looking at it. Will not go to at least this location again. Also, China Fun right down the road serves the same things and more. Their prices are higher but you get double what you would get at Panda Express and the meat is larger. Not cut into bad, charcoal.
When I first walked in the place looked very nice and clean. As I got to the counter the woman behind the counter help me decide what I wanted to get. She was a very nice and helpful.

I want to put my honesty into this review. I have had only 1 bad encounter out of the 15 times I've been here. One drive thru lady gave me a rude/mean look after I asked for some sauce. People over the counter are cool. Food is good and will fill you up
This is always a clean place but I have to say that I dont care much for the staff.  Food is fine & it's a good place for a quick bite
Friendly staff. Very clean restaurant. Quick service. Food was good and always fresh. üëç

results.adr_address: 4614 US-90, Pace, FL 32571, USA
results.name: Jimmy John's

reviews.text:
Definitely not "freaky fast".

It's a Jimmy John's. However, this particular location does not seem to pay attention to mobile orders at all. I have visited 6 times between 2018 December and 2019 April. For each visit, I placed a mobile order 4‚Äì11 minutes prior to arriving. Every time I arrived, there were 2 or more employees present and 0 other customers in the queue. For every single visit, preparation of my order was not started until AFTER I arrived. This is not the speed of service I expect from a chain that advertises itself as "freaky fast". I think it's more appropriate to describe it as an "average chain sandwich shop" in 2019.

I loved their food! I got a club porker, #17, on wheat and it was delicious! The wheat bread is amazing, I definitely recommend. The service was great and the people are super nice. I‚Äôm so glad they opened here! Definitely going back.

I love Jimmy John‚Äôs, but this store wouldn‚Äôt deliver outside a 5 mile radius from the store (They wouldn‚Äôt deliver to the 5pts area). Speaking as a consumer, a five mile delivery radius is too small to justify paying any additional delivery surcharge. I would simply drive out to get it myself. Guess my money goes to someone else.

Very accommodating! I went to make a delivery and found that I couldnt get delivery to my area, although I live very close. When I called, I was told I lived just out of delivery range but they'd deliver to me anyways! Thank you very much, Gerald!

I had Jimmy Johns the other day, and the food was amazing. They had a wide selection of food and their customer service was amazing. They treated me like royalty and the food only added on to the amazing experience. I definitly recommend going to jimmy johns. Can‚Äôt wait to go back and get another sandwich.

results.adr_address: 4741 US-90, Pace, FL 32571, USA
results.name: Moe's Southwestern Grill

reviews.text: This place was very fun! The kids enjoyed their food and I liked their wide selection of items. I got the nachos and was over-stuffed from the large portion! (YUM!) Seriously could not finish my food.  The place was amazingly spotless and very busy when we came. The staff was not only friendly, but patient with us, even though they were slammed. Kudos to them!

I always enjoy my visits to Moe's but I have to say that I'm not a fan of the new chicken choices.  They are both too spicy.  The original chicken was just right for those of us with fussy tummies.  Next time I'll keep it all vegetarian.
Just had the "First rule of Chicken Club" Fantastic... Almost noone here at 430 on a Sunday.. Super easy menu an plenty of seating.
Moes is always good but the young ladies working there last night were superb. Restaurant was clean, food was far superior to most fast foods and the folks were great on service. We will be back.
Love Moes! Their reward system is actually worth it unlike most other apps and point systems.

results.adr_address: 4739 US-90, Pace, FL 32571-1403, USA
results.name: Publix Super Market at Santa Rosa Commons

reviews.text: Once again the drop off/pick up window has a truck sitting there waiting for the pharmacy to fill there prescription. 15 minutes go by before I witness any action at the window. Then it's another 8 minutes before the truck driver gets their prescription. Then they start their truck and leave. I've always been told that I can't do that I can only drop mine off then come back to get them. So I wasted 22 minutes waiting for one vehicle, to do what I've been told isn't allowed. Then I get to the window and get my medication in 5 minutes. If it's a true drop off and pick up window. Why does this happen so often??
I always love going to Publix...got great deals today!! The bakery, produce and meat is always fresh!!! The employees are so friendly, nice and helpful!!!
Always excellent when I go in there. Very clean and the employees are always super friendly!
After a great experience with the pharmacy, I have considered changing my "pharmacy of record" to Publix.
Very delicious food. There subs, Fresh Fruit, and other deli items are extremely tasty all the way around.

results.adr_address: 5129 Dogwood Dr, Milton, FL 32570-4578, USA
results.name: David's Catfish House

reviews.text: Service was fast and friendly.  I was with a few people and everyone that got catfish said it was amazing.  I got the all u can eat shrimp...way over cooked and rubbery. Their coleslaw is excellent.

Our first time eating at David's and we had no idea they closed at 9. We showed up late (8:40) with our 7 year old daughter, on a Friday, hungry and tired from the week. The tables were put up and they looked closed. We were greeted with a smile and "do not worry you are fine".  Our server, David, was so cool about us being late, gave us excellent service, and even went above and beyond to make our dining experience a positive one. He was attentive, funny, and even took the time to put my daughters drawing up for show. Oh and the food...   Excellent. I have nothing but good things to say about Davids. We will go back. Only earlier.

I asked for the buffet and was charged for the buffet price though I only received one plate. I was informed with two options, popcorn shrimp or gumbo shrimp. When the waitress came back I was told I don't get the buffet with the gumbo shrimp, "I didn't know you wanted the buffet". Ok...so I'm getting charged $16 for two fillets of catfish and 8 shrimp and two sides. Definitely could've went elsewhere with my money and will be sure to do so in the future. Make sure your waitress/waiter knows you want the buffet!

So disappointed with our experience last night. Usually David's is wonderful and the food is great.I can't imagine what happened. My sister ordered  the shrimp and grits and my friend ordered the all you can eat peel and eat shrimp anD catfish special. When my sister's order arrived the grits were so salty that the food was inedible...in fact all the grits were too salty mine included. She ordered a new plate of blackened catfish that took almost 45 minutes to reach our table. Meanwhile our friend asked for a refill on his shrimp and that took 20 minutes to get to the table. I would think on an all you can eat night the shrimp would be a ready available!  I am not sure who finally attended our table but she did say that blackened catfish takes a really long time to cook...really? Anyway I hope that this  was a one shot deal and that David's can get their act back together!
Very nice comfortable restaurant. The fried catfish was very tasty. They serve both boneless fillets and bone in catfish. They have other fish and seafood. I would definitely recommend.

results.adr_address: 6645 US-90, Milton, FL 32570, USA
results.name: Texas Roadhouse

reviews.text: I noticed my food tasted odd and that's when I saw my fork and knife were dirty. They had food caked on them. We waited 20 minutes to show our waitress and she never came back so we told another waitress. The second waitress told the manager who came over and grabbed all the silverware and said "what do you want me to do about it?" and walked away. We waited another 10 minutes and our waitress finally showed up with the check. No help from the manager at all. I hadn't eaten hardly anything and they complained about having to get me a to go box. The next day I had food poisoning. We were told Texas Roadhouse was a great place to go. We were just visiting the area and spotted one and decided to try it. I DO NOT recommend Texas Roadhouse! Very horrible experience!!!!!!

Me and my girlfriend was seated and was looking forward to a good meal cause we haven't been to roadhouse in a few months . We was greeted and served our drink pretty quick and then ordered some appetizers that came out at a pretty decent time. The only thing we didn't get was some little plates that they serve give when you receive your appetizer. Att this time our server wasn't anywhere to be found to get them. About 10 minutes later we was able to get one of the other waitresses to get use some plates.  Then it was about an hour before we received our entrees that was not correct. Mind you we still haven't seen or waitress for about another 5 minutes after that.  What I did notice was her stopping and looking at our table and going the other way.  What started out looking like a good dinner turned into a vanishing act by our waitress. The only time she hurried after getting our drinks was to bring my check.  Will not go back to that Texas roadhouse and if we do I will leaves if I get this waitress again

Only waited 15 minutes.  The waiter Tyler was excellent. Value for what you paid for was very good.  Our waiter noticed we didn't get enough boneless wings on our appetizer and promptly went and got more.  The green beans were awesome.  I will return.

Delisious food!  The steaks and fried pickles are exceptional!  It is always packed, but certainly worth the wait!  Fun atmosphere and friendly staff!  Make sure you try the fried pickles!  The manager always comes around to greet you and make sure your food is to your liking.

Service was great. Food mediocre. I ordered ribs and they came out cold. Our server was eager to fix the problem and my new ribs were steamy!
Love the honey butter as always!
Had the loaded fries which were delicious and the salad was great too. Hard to mess up a salad!
